div.div: Shingeki no Kyojin: The Final Season

It’s been four years since the Scout Regiment reached the shoreline, and the world looks different now. Things are heating up as the fate of the Scout Regiment—and the people of Paradis—are determined at last. However, Eren is missing. Will he reappear before age-old tensions between Marleyans and Eldians result in the war of all wars?
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Timid Tadano is a total wallflower, and that’s just the way he likes it. But all that changes when he finds himself alone in a classroom on the first day of high school with the legendary Komi. He quickly realizes she isn’t aloof—she’s just super awkward. Now he’s made it his mission to help her on her quest to make 100 friends!
(Source: Viz Media)
100-nichi Go ni Shinu Akuyaku Reijou wa Mainichi ga Totemo Tanoshii.

"You will die in 100 days." Duchess Lelouche received the prophesy from God. Her fiancé, the Crown Prince, has been distracted by other women and is said to be on the verge of breaking off their engagement... And even if Lelouche knew the future, she still couldn't change the fact that she was going to die. But she can change the way she dies, and the effects of her death - or so she was told. So she made a bet with God.
"If I may die beautifully, please reward me." "If you do good. I will give you whatever you want in your next life." Now Lelouche will act to support the family she is leaving behind, and fight the "conspiracy" that will lead to her eventual death...
(Source: SB Creative, translated)

He and she were enemies. Until he knew he had the same loneliness in a dichotomized world. They are cheap, strong, and never die. The ultimate life regeneration system "Arcadia" was born from teenage soldiers who fight by making full use of the complex regeneration <Respawn>. They were invincible boys and girls (children who transcended death) who died on the battlefield and revived. The forefront of the war in which the two great powers compete for hegemony. Akihito, a boy who leads a platoon as an ace of the United States Army, is ordered to collect confidential information that is inevitable to be wiped out because of his poor performance. However, Akihito, who has kept his companions in an unexpected battle and collapse, is isolated deep underground where complex regeneration <respawn> is impossible, along with his fateful nemesis, the elite girl Philia of the Federal Army. Two people who have opposite personalities and skills and have the worst compatibility will cooperate and aim to return to the ground. The story of the encounter and resonance between him and her who continued to die on the battlefield that never died begins!
<i>Notes: - Winner of the Gold Award in the 28th Dengeki Novel Prize.
